<section>
  <h2>
    About our work
  </h2>
  <p>
     Our team develops an ultra-lightweight data recording and visualization tool called <a href="https://www.simple.org/">Simple</a> that is used by thousands of healthcare workers in India, Bangladesh, and Ethiopia to manage 800,000+ patients with hypertension and diabetes. We're also piloting software for hypertension control in Nigeria.
  </p>
  <p>
    Simple is software that saves lives. Our Android app is used by nurses and healthcare workers in thousands of clinics every day, recording basic patient details, blood pressures, and medications. It enables doctors to track patient treatment over time and remind patients to return for care, both critical elements for controlling high blood pressures. Our app is designed offline-first, allowing it to function quickly and reliably in environments with limited network access.
    <p>
    <p>We also provide a web dashboard to healthcare workers and public health experts, enabling them to see where and how people are getting healthier. This dashboard is vital to helping improve blood pressure control rates across large populations, but also includes detailed information to help improve individual clinics.
  </p>
  <p>
    Learn more about the Simple project at <a href="https://www.simple.org/">Simple.org</a> and in <a href="https://www.simple.org/blog/what-we-are-learning">this article</a>.
  </p>
</section>

